============================================================

Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/21-f1e3c51/improvement-plan.md`.

**Key findings:**

1. **Pattern F root cause is a bug** — `BARSZCZ` has 14.3% vowel ratio, below the 15% garbled threshold. Polish consonant clusters (`szcz`, `cz`, `rz`) naturally produce low vowel ratios. The burst detector eats it, breaking ALL_CAPS coalescence.

2. **Pattern C is mostly missing section labels** — "SERVING SUGGESTION:", "GLAZE:", "INSTRUKCJE:", "For the sauce:" are all structural headers not yet in `SECTION_LABELS`. Straightforward additions.

3. **Pattern A is a one-liner fix** — trailing page numbers after 3+ spaces: `\s{3,}\d{1,4}\s*$`.

4. **Patterns B and I are evaluation harness issues** (13 failures total) — OCR char normalization and Unicode NFC normalization in `titles_match`, not extractor changes.

The plan addresses all 40 failures with 10 discrete changes ordered by priority. Changes 1-6 (32 failures) are low-risk and high-confidence. Changes 7-10 need more care.
