{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SFVcMNfEUUBDF9nG3rXKmj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→VEGETABLE SIDES                         145\n     2→\n     3→Braised Fennel with Tomato\n     4→\n     5→Ingredients:\n     6→3 medium fennel bulbs\n     7→2 tablespoons olive oil\n     8→1 large onion, diced\n     9→4 cloves garlic, min-\n    10→  ced\n    11→1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n    12→1/2 cup vegetable broth 233\n    13→2 tablespoons white wine vinegar\n    14→1 teaspoon sugar\n    15→1 bay leaf\n    16→1/2 teaspoon fennel seed\n    17→Salt and pepper to taste\n    18→\n    19→Method:\n    20→1. Trim fennel bulbs and cut into quarters\n    21→2. Heat olive oil in large braising pot\n    22→3. Add onion and cook until soft, 5 minutes\n    23→4. Add garlic and cook 1 minute more\n    24→5. Stir in diced tomatoes with their juice\n    25→6. Add vegetable broth and vinegar\n    26→7. Season with sugar, bay leaf, fennel seed\n    27→8. Arrange fennel quarters in pot\n    28→9. Bring to simmer and cover partially\n    29→10. Braise for 25-30 minutes until tender\n    30→11. Season with salt and pepper to taste\n    31→\n    32→Serving: Serve warm as side dish with roasted\n    33→meats or fish. Also excellent at room tem-\n    34→perature as part of antipasto platter.\n    35→\n    36→Serves 4-6      Prep 10 min     Cook 35 min\n    37→\n    38→Page 145-146\n    39→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MVBX8ZjctKyB5aUx7MQRdm","session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"e4613f1d-1dce-466a-bc7b-ac578068f733"}
