{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MkAz6LMQJVkEy9h9Ah513o","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→minutes or until slightly reduced. In a hot pan with oil, sear\n     2→the duck breasts skin side down for 5 minutes. Flip and cook\n     3→until medium rare, about 3 minutes more. Rest for ½ cup plus ı tablespoon\n     4→before serving.\n     5→\n     6→Drizzle the pan juices over nto a loured work counter, cooling\n     7→slightly as it firms. The glaze should be amber colored and glossy\n     8→in the afternoon light streaming throught the window. Season with\n     9→fleur de sel and white pepper.\n    10→\n    11→NOTE: This recipe requires no chilling time between kneading nto a smooth\n    12→dough ball ¼ teaspoon nutmeg, ground cloves and 225°C/435-VI0 oven\n    13→temperature. The original version comes from Burgundy, but modern variations\n    14→include fresh tarragon rather than dried herbs. When you press the meat with\n    15→your finger, it should spring back halfway.\n    16→\n    17→INGREDIENTS (serves 8):\n    18→- 2 lbs duck breast, trimmed\n    19→- 3 tablespoons unsalted butter\n    20→- 2 shallots, minced\n    21→- ½ cup red wine\n    22→- Fresh thyme\n    23→- Salt and pepper\n    24→\n    25→GRILLED HALIBUT WITH LEMON BUTTER\n    26→\n    27→INGREDIENTS:\n    28→- 4 halibut fillets, 6 oz each\n    29→- 6 tablespoons unsalted butter\n    30→- 2 lemons\n    31→- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n    32→- Fresh dill\n    33→- Sea salt and cracked pepper\n    34→\n    35→INSTRUCTIONS:\n    36→1. Pat halibut dry with paper towels. Season generously with salt and pepper.\n    37→2. Heat cast iron grill to high heat, lightly oil the grates.\n    38→3. Combine butter, lemon zest, garlic, and dill in a small bowl.\n    39→4. Grill halibut 4-5 minutes per side, basting with lemon butter.\n    40→5. Transfer to serving plates, top with additional lemon butter and dill.\n    41→\n    42→SERVING SUGGESTION:\n    43→Serve with roasted asparagus and new potatoes. A crisp Sauvignon Blanc pairs well.\n    44→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MVBX8ZjctKyB5aUx7MQRdm","session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"cb1258b0-f3da-41d3-bd17-a0f6937f6884"}
