{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QbVjEHXS1bEa19wzaruwk5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Chleb Żytni\n     2→Rye Bread / Pain de Seigle\n     3→\n     4→DROŻDŻE I ZARABIANIE / DOUGH & FERMENTATION:\n     5→- 500g medium rye flour\n     6→- 250g bread wheat flour\n     7→- 7g instant yeast\n     8→- 350ml lukewarm water\n     9→- 10g salt\n    10→- 15g sugar\n    11→- 30g rye sourdough starter (optional)\n    12→- 10g caraway seeds\n    13→- 1 tbsp diastatic malt (optional)\n    14→\n    15→INSTRUKCJA / INSTRUCTIONS:\n    16→\n    17→Mix rye flour, wheat flour, yeast, and salt in large bowl. Combine water, sugar, and\n    18→caraway seeds separately. Add wet mixture to dry ingredients, stirring until shaggy dough\n    19→forms. Cover and rest 20 minutes.\n    20→\n    21→Turn dough onto floured surface and knead 8-10 minutes until elastic. Oil should coat\n    22→outside. Form into ball, place in oiled bowl, cover with towel.\n    23→\n    24→First rise: 1.5-2 hours at room temperature until doubled. Punch down, shape into loaf.\n    25→Second rise: 45 minutes in floured proofing basket or lined bowl.\n    26→\n    27→Heat Dutch oven in 450°F oven for 30 minutes. Score top of loaf with sharp knife.\n    28→Transfer to hot Dutch oven and cover with lid.\n    29→\n    30→Bake covered 35 minutes, then remove lid and bake additional 25-30 minutes until deep\n    31→golden brown. Loaf should sound hollow when tapped on bottom.\n    32→\n    33→Cool completely on wire rack (crucial step for proper crumb structure).\n    34→\n    35→NOTES: Rye bread keeps well wrapped in cloth for 4-5 days. Slices better when day old.\n    36→Serves 8-10 slices per loaf. Very traditional Polish everyday bread.\n    37→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MVBX8ZjctKyB5aUx7MQRdm","session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"1d838353-6abf-462e-9fd9-9e1e040173a1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0134FnVai9qnfqyo6j4XYszD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→WIOSNA | Zupy\n     2→PRZYGOTOWANIE 15 MIN | GOTOWANIE 40 MIN\n     3→DLA 6 OSÓB\n     4→\n     5→MINESTRONE SOUP\n     6→\n     7→Classic Italian vegetable soup with pasta and beans.\n     8→\n     9→INGREDIENTS:\n    10→- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n    11→- 1 large onion, diced\n    12→- 3 carrots, cut into chunks\n    13→- 3 celery stalks, chopped\n    14→- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n    15→- 8 oz green beans, cut into 1-inch pieces\n    16→- 2 medium zucchini, cut into half-moons\n    17→- 1 can (15 oz) diced tomatoes\n    18→- 1 can (15 oz) cannellini beans, drained\n    19→- 6 cups vegetable or chicken broth\n    20→- 1 cup small pasta (ditalini or elbow)\n    21→- ¼ cup fresh basil, chopped\n    22→- 1 teaspoon dried oregano\n    23→- Salt and pepper to taste\n    24→- Parmesan cheese for serving\n    25→\n    26→INSTRUCTIONS:\n    27→1. Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat.\n    28→2. Sauté onion, carrots, and celery for 5 minutes until softened.\n    29→3. Add garlic and cook for 1 minute until fragrant.\n    30→4. Pour in broth and bring to a boil.\n    31→5. Add green beans, zucchini, tomatoes, beans, and oregano.\n    32→6. Simmer for 20 minutes until vegetables are tender.\n    33→7. Add pasta and cook according to package directions.\n    34→8. Stir in fresh basil just before serving.\n    35→9. Season with salt and pepper.\n    36→10. Ladle into bowls and top with grated Parmesan cheese.\n    37→\n    38→SERVING:\n    39→Serve hot with crusty bread and a drizzle of good quality olive oil.\n    40→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MVBX8ZjctKyB5aUx7MQRdm","session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"5b44b159-e7f6-48ce-9e2d-e20aa7229ede"}
