{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WJ2dnSocis7KXHnre2qCzj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→BARSZCZ\n     2→UKRAIŃSKI\n     3→\n     4→Ingredienty (dla 6 osób):\n     5→- 1 kg buraków\n     6→- 2 marchewki\n     7→- 3 ziemniaki średnie\n     8→- 1 cebula\n     9→- 2 liście laurowe\n    10→- 1,5 litra wody\n    11→- 2 łyżki octu winnego\n    12→- Sól i pieprz\n    13→- Świeży koperek\n    14→\n    15→Przygotowanie:\n    16→1. Obrać buraki i marchewkę, pokroić w słupki.\n    17→2. Ziemniaki pokroić na kostki.\n    18→3. Cebulę pokroić na połówki.\n    19→4. Wrzucić buraki, marchewkę, ziemniaki i cebulę do garnka.\n    20→5. Wlać wodę, dodać liście laurowe.\n    21→6. Gotować 45 minut do miękkości.\n    22→7. Dodać ocet, sól i pieprz do smaku.\n    23→8. Podawać ze śmietaną i świeżym koprem.\n    24→\n    25→Wskazówka:\n    26→Możesz dodać białą fasolę lub bób dla większej pożywności.\n    27→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MVBX8ZjctKyB5aUx7MQRdm","session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"240aabca-4e14-4a9a-9d69-511577ded491"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CCAEuvCeVWLZ6NbZqgQXjo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Karp Pieczony\n     2→Roasted Carp with Almond & Raisin Sauce\n     3→\n     4→SKŁADNIKI / INGREDIENTS:\n     5→- 1 whole carp (2-3 kg), cleaned and gutted\n     6→- 1 large onion, sliced\n     7→- 3 carrots, sliced into rounds\n     8→- 2 celery stalks, chunked\n     9→- 4 bay leaves\n    10→- 6 peppercorns\n    11→- 1/2 cup raisins, soaked in warm water\n    12→- 3/4 cup roasted almonds, coarsely chopped\n    13→- 4 tbsp butter\n    14→- 2 tbsp flour\n    15→- 1 cup fish or vegetable stock\n    16→- 1 tbsp Dijon mustard\n    17→- 2 tbsp apple cider vinegar\n    18→- Salt and pepper to taste\n    19→- Fresh parsley for garnish\n    20→\n    21→PRZYGOTOWANIE / PREPARATION:\n    22→\n    23→Score skin of carp diagonally at 2-inch intervals, being careful not to pierce flesh.\n    24→This helps seasonings penetrate and skin crisps properly.\n    25→\n    26→In large roasting pan, arrange half the vegetables (onion, carrot, celery) and all bay\n    27→leaves and peppercorns. Lay carp on vegetables, season inside cavity and outside with\n    28→salt and pepper.\n    29→\n    30→Top fish with remaining vegetables. Dot with 2 tbsp butter. Roast uncovered at 375°F\n    31→for 35-40 minutes until flesh flakes easily.\n    32→\n    33→While fish roasts, make sauce: melt remaining butter, whisk in flour to create roux.\n    34→Toast 1 minute, add stock slowly, stirring constantly. Add drained raisins, chopped\n    35→almonds, mustard, and vinegar. Simmer 5 minutes until thickened.\n    36→\n    37→Remove carp from oven and carefully transfer to serving platter. Strain roasting pan\n    38→juices and add to almond sauce.\n    39→\n    40→Pour warm sauce over fish, garnish with fresh parsley. Serve with boiled potatoes or\n    41→rye bread to absorb delicious sauce.\n    42→\n    43→NOTES: Carp is traditional Christmas Eve fish in Poland. Flesh is delicate, sweet.\n    44→Serves 4-6. Sauce can be made ahead.\n    45→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MVBX8ZjctKyB5aUx7MQRdm","session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"aa92c575-3fbd-4583-8002-d6fb4a41ca74"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L9q5ewcpdp9QwjGbqU5b5a","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→SOURDOUGH BREAD WITH SEEDS : SOURDOUGH WITH HERBS\n     2→\n     3→SOURDOUGH BREAD WITH SEEDS\n     4→\n     5→Ingredients:\n     6→- 500 g sourdough starter\n     7→- 350 ml water\n     8→- 500 g bread flour\n     9→- 10 g salt\n    10→- 50 g mixed seeds (sunflower, pumpkin, sesame)\n    11→- Cornmeal for dusting\n    12→\n    13→Instructions:\n    14→1. Mix sourdough starter, water, and flour in bowl\n    15→2. Let rest 30 minutes (autolyse)\n    16→3. Add salt and knead thoroughly\n    17→4. Mix in seeds evenly\n    18→5. Bulk fermentation 4-6 hours at room temperature\n    19→6. Shape and proof overnight in banneton\n    20→7. Score with sharp knife\n    21→8. Bake at 450°F for 35-40 minutes in Dutch oven\n    22→\n    23→SOURDOUGH WITH HERBS\n    24→\n    25→Ingredients:\n    26→- 500 g sourdough starter\n    27→- 350 ml water\n    28→- 500 g bread flour\n    29→- 10 g salt\n    30→- 2 tbsp fresh rosemary, chopped\n    31→- 1 tbsp fresh thyme, chopped\n    32→- Cornmeal for dusting\n    33→\n    34→Instructions:\n    35→1. Mix sourdough starter, water, and flour\n    36→2. Let rest 30 minutes for autolyse\n    37→3. Add salt and knead thoroughly\n    38→4. Mix in herbs evenly throughout\n    39→5. Bulk fermentation 4-6 hours at room temperature\n    40→6. Shape and proof overnight in banneton\n    41→7. Score with sharp knife\n    42→8. Bake at 450°F for 35-40 minutes in Dutch oven\n    43→\n    44→Each makes 1 loaf\n    45→Serves 8 people per loaf\n    46→Total time: 12 hours plus overnight\n    47→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MVBX8ZjctKyB5aUx7MQRdm","session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"13588461-d73b-42ab-ba71-f460e8965b9d"}
