{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VCkCn5CQch5EGBbuiRDHbu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Zupa Jarzynowa z Kluskami\n     2→(Vegetable Soup with Dumplings)\n     3→\n     4→CZĘŚĆ 1: ZUPA / PART 1: SOUP BASE\n     5→\n     6→SKŁADNIKI / INGREDIENTS:\n     7→- 2 tbsp butter or sunflower oil\n     8→- 1 large  onion, diced finely\n     9→- 3  carrots, sliced thin (approximately  0.5 cm thickness)\n    10→- 2 parsnips, diced\n    11→- 1 small celeriac root, peeled, cubed (important!)\n    12→- 3 medium potatoes (waxy variety preferre\n    13→- 6 cups vegetable or light chicken  broth / stock\n    14→- 2 bay leaves\n    15→- 4-5 fresh thyme sprigs\n    16→- Salt and pepper to taste\n    17→- 1 tbsp fresh dill, chopped fine\n    18→- Squeeze of lemon juice (optional, ~89 adds brightness)\n    19→\n    20→PRZYGOTOWANIE / PREPARATION:\n    21→\n    22→Heat butter in large pot over medium heat. Add diced onion, cook stirring until\n    23→golden and soft (6-8 minutes is ideal – not brown, golden).\n    24→\n    25→Add carrots, parsnips, celeriac. Stir well with wooden spoon, coating vegetables\n    26→in butter. Cook 5 minutes uncovered. Aroma will develop. This step essential for\n    27→flavor development12 in final soup.\n    28→\n    29→Add diced potatoes and broth. Drop in bay leaves and thyme sprigs. Bring mixture\n    30→to boil, then reduce immediately to gentle simmer.\n    31→\n    32→Cook uncovered 25-30 minutes until all vegetables tender when pierced with fork.\n    33→Season with salt, pepper. Remove bay leaves. Stir in fresh dill and optional lemon.\n    34→\n    35→---\n    36→\n    37→CZĘŚĆ 2: KLUSKI / PART 2: DUMPLINGS\n    38→\n    39→SKŁADNIKI / INGREDIENTS FOR DUMPLINGS:\n    40→- 2 cups all-purpose flour\n    41→- 1 egg, room temperature\n    42→- 1/2 tsp salt\n    43→- 4 tbsp cold butter, cubed\n    44→- Approximately 6-7 tbsp lukewarm water  (add gradually – 6 exact)\n    45→- Pinch nutmeg (optional)\n    46→\n    47→PRZYGOTOWANIE / PREPARATION:\n    48→\n    49→In bowl, mix flour and salt. Make well in center. Drop in cubed butter and\n    50→egg. Using fork, incorporate flour gradually into wet ingredients.\n    51→\n    52→Add water slowly, one tablespoon at time. Dough should be soft but not sticky.\n    53→Form into ball, wrap in plastic, rest 15 minutes minimum.\n    54→\n    55→Bring soup to gentle simmer. Using two spoons, drop small dumplings (teaspoon-size)\n    56→directly into simmering soup. They will sink, then rise to surface when cooked.\n    57→\n    58→Continue adding dumplings in batches. Simmer 10 minutes total after last dumpling\n    59→added. Dumplings should be fluffy, light (never heavy or dense – indicates overworking).\n    60→\n    61→Serve hot with fresh dill garnish. Traditional Polish comfort soup served year-round.\n    62→\n    63→NOTES: Zupa Jarzynowa signature Polish dish. Proportions flexible  – adjust vegetables\n    64→based on availability & season. Dumplings can be made ahead (stored in refrigerator).\n    65→Serves 6-8.\n    66→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MVBX8ZjctKyB5aUx7MQRdm","session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"6de7d0b1-f9dc-428e-8711-b950935d9836"}
