CR has mixed case (e.g., `Szarlotka`, `Beef Wellington`), return as-is — only normalize ALL_CAPS\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-29-\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-30-**Before:**\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-31-```typescript\n--\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-34-\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-35-**After:**\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-36-```typescript\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:37:return selected.map((s) => normalizeCase(s.text)).join(\" + \");\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-38-```\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-39-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-40-```typescript\n--\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-43-  \"do\", \"na\", \"po\", \"od\", \"ku\", \"ni\", \"bo\",\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-44-]);\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-45-\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:46:function normalizeCase(text: string): string {\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-47-  if (!isAllCaps(text)) return text;\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-48-  const words = text.split(/\\s+/);\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-49-  return words.map((word, idx) => {\n--\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-316-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-317-### Proposed Change\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-318-\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:319:Add a **parenthetical gloss stripper** as a post-merge normalization step. When a candidate ends with a parenthetical that contains mixed-case English text (a translation/gloss), strip it.\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-320-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-321-```typescript\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:322:function stripParentheticalGloss(text: string): string {\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-323-  // Match trailing parenthetical with mixed-case content (English glosses)\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-324-  // e.g., \"PIEROGI RUSKIE (Boiled Dumplings with Potato and Cheese)\"\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-325-  // but NOT \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS (VARIATION D)\" (ALL_CAPS = part of title)\n--\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-339-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-340-```typescript\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-341-/ In the single-line candidate generation:\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:342:const cleaned = stripParentheticalGloss(line.text);\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-343-if (passesHardFilters(cleaned)) {\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-344-  candidates.push({ text: cleaned, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-345-}\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-346-```\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-347-\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:348:Also handle the case where the parenthetical is on the same OCR line (e.g., `MAKOWIEC (Polish Poppy Seed Cake)`): the strip function handles this since it operates on the text content regardless of how it was assembled.\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-349-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-350-### Expected Impact\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-351-\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:352:Fixes ~5 failures where English glosses contaminate the title. Combined with Change 1 (case normalization), the stripped ALL_CAPS title is then correctly converted to Title Case.\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-353-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-354----\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-355-\n--\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-398-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-399-### Proposed Change\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-400-\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:401:Modify `startsWithNumber` to first try stripping a page-number prefix. If a line matches `^\\d{1,3}\\s{2,}[A-Z]` (1–3 digits, 2+ spaces, then an uppercase letter), strip the number prefix and return the remainder as the candidate text instead of discarding the whole line.\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-402-\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:403:**Implementation:** Rather than changing `startsWithNumber`, add a normalization step in `buildCandidates` that strips page number prefixes before hard filtering:\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-404-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-405-```typescript\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:406:function stripPageNumber(text: string): string {\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-407-  // \"34  Berry Jam\" → \"Berry Jam\"\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-408-  // \"7   Chocolate Cake\" → \"Chocolate Cake\"\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-409-  // Must have 2+ spaces to distinguish from \"2 eggs\" (ingredient)\n--\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-416-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-417-```typescript\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-418-const rawText = line.text;\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:419:const strippedText = stripPageNumber(rawText);\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:420:if (passesHardFilters(strippedText)) {\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:421:  candidates.push({ text: strippedText, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-422-}\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-423-```\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-424-\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:425:**Safety:** The 2+ space requirement prevents stripping ingredient quantities like `2 eggs` or `100g flour`. Page numbers followed by titles always have multiple spaces (typographic convention).\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-426-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-427-### Expected Impact\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-428-\n--\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-461-| 6 | SEZON: metadata pattern | ~2 | None | Trivial |\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-462-| 7 | Strip parenthetical glosses | ~5 | Low | Medium |\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-463-| 8 | Position-aware compound dedup | 1 | Very low | Low |\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md:464:| 9 | Page number prefix stripping | 1 | Low | Low |\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-465-\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-466-**Expected total fixes: 48–52 out of 54 failures**\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-467-**Expected new pass rate: ~96–98%**\n--\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-473-1. Change 1 (case normalization) — biggest win, zero interaction with other changes\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-474-2. Change 2 (commonShort2) — trivial, zero risk\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-plan.md-475-3. Change 6 (SEZON: metadata) — trivial, zero risk\ntools/title-loop/docs/18-1d256ae/improvement-