tle-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-198-```typescript\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:199:const normalized = text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase();\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:200:return SECTION_LABELS.has(normalized);\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-201-```\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-202-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-203-`\"skladniki\"` ≠ `\"składniki\"`, so the check fails. `SKLADNIKI` enters the candidate pool, adding noise to the threshold calculation.\n--\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-207-**File:** `lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-208-**Location:** `isSectionLabel` function (lines 110–113) and `SECTION_LABELS` set (lines 99–108)\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-209-\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:210:**Add a diacritic-stripping utility:**\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-211-```typescript\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:212:function stripDiacritics(text: string): string {\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:213:  return text.normalize(\"NFKD\").replace(/[\\u0300-\\u036f]/g, \"\");\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-214-}\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-215-```\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-216-\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:217:**Update `SECTION_LABELS` to store stripped forms:**\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-218-```typescript\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-219-const SECTION_LABELS = new Set([\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-220-  // English\n--\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-231-**Update `isSectionLabel`:**\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-232-```typescript\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-233-function isSectionLabel(text: string): boolean {\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:234:  const normalized = stripDiacritics(text.trim().replace(/[:.]$/, \"\").toLowerCase());\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:235:  return SECTION_LABELS.has(normalized);\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-236-}\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-237-```\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-238-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-239-### Why this works\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-240-\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:241:- `\"SKLADNIKI\"` → `toLowerCase()` → `\"skladniki\"` → `stripDiacritics()` → `\"skladniki\"` → matches\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:242:- `\"SKŁADNIKI\"` → `toLowerCase()` → `\"składniki\"` → `stripDiacritics()` → `\"skladniki\"` → matches\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:243:- `\"składniki\"` → `stripDiacritics()` → `\"skladniki\"` → matches\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-244-- All three OCR variants now caught\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-245-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-246-### Safety analysis\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-247-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-248-- Unicode NFKD + combining mark removal is a well-established technique, available in all JavaScript engines including Hermes (React Native).\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:249:- No legitimate recipe title would match a section label after diacritic stripping — section labels are structural words (\"ingredients\", \"preparation\"), not food names.\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-250-- English section labels have no diacritics, so they are unaffected.\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-251-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-252-### Expected impact\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-253-\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md:254:Non-blocking for the current failure (SKLADNIKI doesn't win regardless), but eliminates a noise source from the threshold calculation and prevents future regressions where a diacritic-stripped section label could tip the score balance.\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-255-\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-256----\n/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-257-\n--\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-305-   Input: same as above but verify that `firstStructuralHeading` is not the translation line.\ntools/title-loop/docs/16-e59482e/improvement-plan.md-306-   Expected: no structur