{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016Do3pM6rNQdHNJyt8YexLf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→APPETIZERS | Page 23\n     2→\n     3→Herb Marinated Olives\n     4→\n     5→128 | This recipe keeps for several weeks\n     6→\n     7→INGREDIENTS:\n     8→3 cups mixed olives (Kalamata and green)\n     9→6 cloves garlic, smashed\n    10→2 tablespoons fresh rosemary sprigs\n    11→4 sprigs fresh thyme\n    12→2 bay leaves\n    13→1 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n    14→½ cup olive oil\n    15→¼ cup red wine vinegar\n    16→Zest of 1 lemon\n    17→4-5 black peppercorns\n    18→\n    19→INSTRUCTIONS:\n    20→1. Combine olives, garlic, herbs, and pepper flakes in glass jar\n    21→2. Whisk together olive oil, vinegar, and lemon zest\n    22→3. Pour over olives\n    23→4. Seal jar and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving\n    24→5. Shake jar daily for first 3 days to distribute flavors\n    25→6. Keeps up to 4 weeks refrigerated\n    26→\n    27→SERVING SUGGESTION:\n    28→Serve as part of an antipasto platter or alongside cheese and crusty bread.\n    29→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"85535cf7-562c-4674-a2e7-d31a217ff702","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Herb Marinated Olives.generated.21.txt","content":"APPETIZERS | Page 23\n\nHerb Marinated Olives\n\n128 | This recipe keeps for several weeks\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n3 cups mixed olives (Kalamata and green)\n6 cloves garlic, smashed\n2 tablespoons fresh rosemary sprigs\n4 sprigs fresh thyme\n2 bay leaves\n1 teaspoon red pepper flakes\n½ cup olive oil\n¼ cup red wine vinegar\nZest of 1 lemon\n4-5 black peppercorns\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Combine olives, garlic, herbs, and pepper flakes in glass jar\n2. Whisk together olive oil, vinegar, and lemon zest\n3. Pour over olives\n4. Seal jar and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving\n5. Shake jar daily for first 3 days to distribute flavors\n6. Keeps up to 4 weeks refrigerated\n\nSERVING SUGGESTION:\nServe as part of an antipasto platter or alongside cheese and crusty bread.\n","numLines":29,"startLine":1,"totalLines":29}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WEAFoKybqt8HoM71uJR6DD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Page 47 | DESSERTS\n     2→\n     3→Lemon Blueberry Cake\n     4→\n     5→INGREDIENTS:\n     6→2 cups all-purpose flour\n     7→1½ teaspoons baking powder\n     8→½ teaspoon salt\n     9→½ cup (1 stick) butter, softened\n    10→1 cup sugar\n    11→2 large eggs\n    12→½ cup sour cream\n    13→Zest of 2 lemons\n    14→3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n    15→1½ cups fresh blueberries\n    16→2 tablespoons flour for coating berries\n    17→\n    18→GLAZE:\n    19→3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n    20→1 cup powdered sugar\n    21→\n    22→INSTRUCTIONS:\n    23→1. Preheat oven to 350°F\n    24→2. Whisk together flour, baking powder, salt\n    25→3. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy\n    26→4. Beat in eggs one at a time\n    27→5. Alternate adding flour mixture and sour cream\n    28→6. Fold in lemon zest and juice\n    29→7. Toss blueberries with flour coating\n    30→8. Gently fold into batter\n    31→9. Pour into greased 9-inch round pan\n    32→10. Bake 35-40 minutes until golden\n    33→11. Cool completely\n    34→12. Whisk together lemon juice and powdered sugar\n    35→13. Drizzle over cooled cake\n    36→14. Serve at room temperature\n    37→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"884e49be-4e3a-460b-a980-60cd1f97b76d","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Lemon Blueberry Cake.generated.21.txt","content":"Page 47 | DESSERTS\n\nLemon Blueberry Cake\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n2 cups all-purpose flour\n1½ teaspoons baking powder\n½ teaspoon salt\n½ cup (1 stick) butter, softened\n1 cup sugar\n2 large eggs\n½ cup sour cream\nZest of 2 lemons\n3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n1½ cups fresh blueberries\n2 tablespoons flour for coating berries\n\nGLAZE:\n3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice\n1 cup powdered sugar\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Preheat oven to 350°F\n2. Whisk together flour, baking powder, salt\n3. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy\n4. Beat in eggs one at a time\n5. Alternate adding flour mixture and sour cream\n6. Fold in lemon zest and juice\n7. Toss blueberries with flour coating\n8. Gently fold into batter\n9. Pour into greased 9-inch round pan\n10. Bake 35-40 minutes until golden\n11. Cool completely\n12. Whisk together lemon juice and powdered sugar\n13. Drizzle over cooled cake\n14. Serve at room temperature\n","numLines":37,"startLine":1,"totalLines":37}}}
