{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012fSrKqbGtTSfSCahKmTReY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Page 24\n     2→\n     3→Lentil Vegetable Soup\n     4→\n     5→[CLASSIC FALL SOUPS]\n     6→\n     7→INGREDIENTS:\n     8→\n     9→- 1.5 cups dried lentils (brown or green),  rinsed\n    10→- 2 tbsp olive  oil\n    11→- 1 large yellow onion, diced\n    12→- 3 carrots, cut into 1/4-inch rounds\n    13→- 2 celery stalks, sliced on blas\n    14→- 4 cloves garlic, minced (fresh preferred)\n    15→- 3 medium  potatoes, diced (skin on)\n    16→- 6 cups vegetable or  chicken stock\n    17→- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes in juice\n    18→- 1 tsp cumin powder (optional)\n    19→- 2 bay  leaves\n    20→- Salt and pepper to  taste\n    21→- 1 tbsp balsamic vin87egar (fine-\n    22→- Fresh parsley for  garnish\n    23→\n    24→INSTRUCTIONS:\n    25→\n    26→Sort lentils, removing  any stones or debris. Rinse thoroughly under cool\n    27→running water until  water runs clear. (This step: 3-5 minutes)\n    28→\n    29→Heat olive oil in large Dutch  oven or heavy pot over medium heat. Once\n    30→shimmering, add diced onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent\n    31→(approximately 6-8 minutes).\n    32→\n    33→Add carrot, celery slices, and minced garlic cloves. Cook 3  more minutes,\n    34→stirring constantly to prevent garlic from burning (burned  garlic  = bitter\n    35→taste, so watch  carefully!).\n    36→\n    37→Pour in the prepared lentils, diced potatoes, stock, canned  tomatoes\n    38→with juice. Add bay leaves. If using cumin, add now (heav23y spice,\n    39→don't  overdo).\n    40→\n    41→Bring the mixture to a boil over high heat, then immediately  reduce to\n    42→low  heat. Simmer uncovered for 30-35 minutes until lentils are tender\n    43→(not mushy – you want them  to hold shape).\n    44→\n    45→Add balsamic vinegar and salt/pepper to taste. Adjust stock  if soup\n    46→too thick. Serves 6-8 hungry people or 4 with bread for meal.\n    47→\n    48→Garnish with fresh  parsley before serving. Can be made 2-3  days ahead.\n    49→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b8858bc-a11e-49e9-aee6-802d54bbaef0","uuid":"f7f7ad04-9a69-49a0-a8db-9a987af5de56","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Lentil Vegetable Soup.generated.21.txt","content":"Page 24\n\nLentil Vegetable Soup\n\n[CLASSIC FALL SOUPS]\n\nINGREDIENTS:\n\n- 1.5 cups dried lentils (brown or green),  rinsed\n- 2 tbsp olive  oil\n- 1 large yellow onion, diced\n- 3 carrots, cut into 1/4-inch rounds\n- 2 celery stalks, sliced on blas\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced (fresh preferred)\n- 3 medium  potatoes, diced (skin on)\n- 6 cups vegetable or  chicken stock\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes in juice\n- 1 tsp cumin powder (optional)\n- 2 bay  leaves\n- Salt and pepper to  taste\n- 1 tbsp balsamic vin87egar (fine-\n- Fresh parsley for  garnish\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n\nSort lentils, removing  any stones or debris. Rinse thoroughly under cool\nrunning water until  water runs clear. (This step: 3-5 minutes)\n\nHeat olive oil in large Dutch  oven or heavy pot over medium heat. Once\nshimmering, add diced onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent\n(approximately 6-8 minutes).\n\nAdd carrot, celery slices, and minced garlic cloves. Cook 3  more minutes,\nstirring constantly to prevent garlic from burning (burned  garlic  = bitter\ntaste, so watch  carefully!).\n\nPour in the prepared lentils, diced potatoes, stock, canned  tomatoes\nwith juice. Add bay leaves. If using cumin, add now (heav23y spice,\ndon't  overdo).\n\nBring the mixture to a boil over high heat, then immediately  reduce to\nlow  heat. Simmer uncovered for 30-35 minutes until lentils are tender\n(not mushy – you want them  to hold shape).\n\nAdd balsamic vinegar and salt/pepper to taste. Adjust stock  if soup\ntoo thick. Serves 6-8 hungry people or 4 with bread for meal.\n\nGarnish with fresh  parsley before serving. Can be made 2-3  days ahead.\n","numLines":49,"startLine":1,"totalLines":49}}}
